-- Egyptian Stocks: Orascom Telecom Media
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-06-28T13:13:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-28/egyptian-stocks-orascom-telecom-media-south-valley-cement.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30)  added
1.7 percent to 4,708.59 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo, the
highest level in a month. The measure’s 17 percent surge this
week narrowed its quarterly decline to 6.2 percent.  The following shares were active on the Egyptian Exchange.
Stock symbols follow company names.  Housing & Development Bank (HDBK)   increased 1.7 percent
to 11.87 Egyptian pounds. The Cairo-based lender agreed in
principle with  Libya ’s Bank of Commerce & Development to provide
services to Egyptians in the North African country as well as
starting a joint real estate company.  Orascom Telecom Media & Technology Holding SAE (OTMT)  
rose to the highest level in more than two months, advancing 2.1
percent to 1.48 pounds. Shareholders of the Cairo-based company
are due to vote today on a dividend distribution of 1.05 pounds
per share.  South Valley Cement (SVCE)   gained 4.3 percent to 3.43
pounds, the highest level in more than three months. The Cairo-
based producer of the building material will buy back 24.3
million shares at 3.5 pounds each.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A. Namatalla in Cairo at 
